<TITLE> Ashley Cole back in Chelsea squad for Spurs game </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 COBHAM, Apr 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - England defender Ashley Cole could return ahead of schedule for Premier League leaders Chelsea in Saturday's game at Tottenham Hotspur (5:30pm), manager Carlo Ancelotti said on Friday. Cole, England's first-choice left back, broke his left ankle at Everton at the start of February. Ancelotti had said before he could be back for the game against Stoke City on Apr 25 but declared him 100 percent fit already. "Ashley Cole is in the squad tomorrow," he told reporters at Chelsea's training ground. "He is ready, he's fit, he's totally recovering from his injury and he will start from the bench tomorrow." Cole's return is also good news for England, with the World Cup starting in South Africa on Jun
